There are many ways to rotate RaspberryPi output screens using xrandr command, screen configuration and by editing 
the boot configuration file and we have tried and successfully implemented.

By writing following commands in terminal of Rarspberry Pi-
	
	DISPLAY=:0 xrandr --output HDMI-1 --rotate right
 	DISPLAY=:0 xrandr --output HDMI-2 --rotate right

By Editing boot configuration file-
	
	sudo nano /boot/config.txt
		display_hdmi-1_rotate=0	
		display_hdmi-2_rotate=0

Using Screen Configuraion-
	-Click the Pi icon
	-Go to Preferences
	-Click on screen Configuration
	-Go to Configure and then screens->HDMI1/2
	-Orientation->Right 
	-Lastly click on Apply changes.
  
